						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is damaged and last few lines are missing. It records the royal order sent to the assembly of Nallūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Amarabhuyaṅkara-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Vīrachōḻa vaḷa-nāḍu and the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Veḷḷānūr, of giving particular amount of paddy to the person as <hi rend="italic">pūjāvritti,</hi> who was doing worship in the temple of Tirumurugaṉpūṇḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
